claim.claim-text:
5. A method for providing a Digital Rights Management (DRM) service, comprising:
Determining, by a Media Presentation Description (MPD) information controller, a DRM system required in each of representations of content provided by an adaptive streaming service;
classifying, by the Media Presentation Description (MPD) information controller, the representations into one or more groups according to predetermined criteria, and generating representation group information representing the classified groups;
configuring, by the Media Presentation Description (MPD) information controller, Media Presentation Description (MPD) information by inserting content protection information including the representation group information and information about DRM systems corresponding to the representation group information; and
transmitting, by a transceiver, the MPD information to a user terminal receiving the content,
wherein the representation group information is information about each of representation groups generated by a combination of at least two representations among representations of the content according to predetermined criteria.

9. A user terminal apparatus for providing a Digital Rights Management (DRM) service, comprising:
a transceiver for receiving Media Presentation Description (MPD) information for content provided by an adaptive streaming service;
a media composition controller for checking, from the MPD information, representation group information representing a combination of at least one representation among representations of the content, and determining multiple DRM systems applied for decryption of the content by analyzing content protection information corresponding to the representation group information;
a DRM selector for selecting a DRM satisfying a predetermined condition from among the determined DRM systems; and
a decrypter for decrypting the content using the selected DRM,
wherein the representation group information is information about each of representation groups generated by a combination of at least two representations among representations of the content according to predetermined criteria.

13. A method for providing a Digital Rights Management (DRM) service in a user terminal apparatus, comprising:
receiving, by a transceiver, Media Presentation Description (MPD) information for content provided by an adaptive streaming service;
checking, by a media composition controller, from the MPD information, representation group information representing a combination of at least one representation among representations of the content;
determining, by the media composition controller, multiple DRM systems applied for decryption of the content by analyzing content protection information corresponding to the representation group information;
selecting, by a DRM selector, a DRM satisfying a predetermined condition from among the determined DRM systems; and
decrypting, by a decrypter, the content using the selected DRM,
wherein the representation group information is information about each of representation groups generated by a combination of at least two representations among representations of the content according to predetermined criteria.
